# Data mapping & demos (Daniel)

## Data mapping (canonical)

All **Account 360 data mapping** workfiles (CSV, XLSX, field maps, Louise collaboration sheets):

- **`Data/mapping/`** at project root — this is the **single working source of truth**.
- Do **not** leave new mapping artefacts only under `exports/`. Reserve `exports/` for **standalone HTML/PPTX launcher-style** artefacts unless the user says otherwise.

## Version history (milestones)

When producing a **new milestone** snapshot of mapping (after meaningful changes), **also** copy the current contents of `Data/mapping/` to:

- **`Account 360 Demo versions/YYYY-MM-DD_data-mapping/`** (use authoritative date from user context).

Keep filenames stable inside that folder so diffs stay readable.

## Desktop mirror

After writing or updating mapping files under `Data/mapping/`, **mirror the same files** to:

- **`/Users/daniel.rosemberg/Desktop/Account 360 MVP/Data/mapping/`**

So Daniel’s organized Desktop workspace stays aligned with git.

Use `mkdir -p` and `cp` (or rsync). Do **not** invent alternate Desktop folders unless Daniel asks.

